# Consider the following folder structure in Windows. We will push "folder2" along with "file1" to GITHUB REPO using GIT_BASH.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
folder1/
├── folder2/
└── file1.txt
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# STEPS :
#1) In order push the "folder2" and "file1". You have be in the "folder1". [pwd --> /root/folder1 ]
#2) Use "git init" command to initiate ".git" folder in the "folder1". 
#3) "ls -a" --> to see ".git" folder.
#4) "git branch -M main" --> to force rename "local branch name" to "main".
#5) "git remote -v" Command to check whether remote repository connected or not. you will see the username along with reponame like "<username/repo.git>", if connected. If not, not response.
#6) Adding remote repo --> "git remote add origin https://github.com/manojpodugu/temp.git"   
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
